            <div class="text-content field field--name-comment-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item comment__text-content"><p>Hi,&nbsp;David!</p><p>You will want to gently <a style="box-shadow:rgb(69, 87, 117) 0px -2px 0px 0px inset;box-sizing:border-box;color:rgb(69, 87, 117);overflow-wrap:break-word;text-decoration:none !important;transition:box-shadow 0.3s cubic-bezier(0.55, 0.085, 0, 0.99) 0s;" href="https://www.almanac.com/blog/gardening/garden-journal/mulching-guide-benefits-mulch">mulch</a>&nbsp;carrots to retain moisture, speed germination, and block the sun from hitting the&nbsp;roots&nbsp;directly.</p><p>Fertilize 5 to 6 weeks after sowing. (We recommend a low-nitrogen fertilizer as excess nitrogen in the soil promotes top, or foliage,&nbsp;growthâ€”not&nbsp;roots.)</p></div>
