<article  data-comment-user-id="0" id="comment-132406" class="comment by-anonymous" role="article" data-drupal-selector="comment">
  <div class="comment__text-wrapper">
    <footer class="comment__meta">
      <p class="comment__author"><span>Elina (not verified)</span></p>
      <p class="comment__time">1 year 5 months ago</p>
                    <p class="visually-hidden">In reply to <a href="/comment/128722#comment-128722" class="permalink" rel="bookmark" hreflang="en">I live in AB. I have beenâ€¦</a> by <span>jr (not verified)</span></p>
          </footer>
    <div class="comment__content">
      
            <div class="text-content field field--name-comment-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item comment__text-content"><p>Try planting them in the summer and harvesting after first few frosts. Look at the maturity date on the seed package, and count back that many days from when you start getting frosts in your area, and that would be the date to plant the carrots. Big types of carrots should be planted for fall/early winter harvest, and not in the spring for summer harvest.</p>
</div>
